cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.CV 

The paper deals with the modeling and simulation of traffic flow and crowd movement, which involves interactions between pedestrians and cars in many situations. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes an emotion-based crowd simulation model, which could also place it in the Social and Information Sciences (cs.SI) or Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper compares the resulting behaviors with real-world video sequences, indicating that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
